    <p>
    <h4>Corrected Information</h4>
    </p>
    <p><S>only done with cgi.</S></p>Iron Man's suit was not only CGI. While the vast majority of the action footage
    throughout the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU) relied heavily on computer-generated imagery, the early movies
    featured incredibly detailed, real physical armor pieces built for Robert Downey Jr. to wear on set.

    <h2>Early Life and Career</h2>
    <p><i>Anthony Edward "Tony" Stark</i> is a fictional character and the main protagonist of the Marvel Cinematic
        Universe's Iron Man film series. He is a billionaire industrialist and engineer who becomes a superhero after
        being kidnapped and forced to build a weapon for his captors. Instead, he builds a suit of powered armor and
        escapes, using it to fight crime and protect the world.</p>

    <h2>Important Achievements</h2>
    <p><small><mark><i>Contains Avengers Endgame Spoilers</small></mark></p>
    </h3></i>
    <p>*The Origin: Built a high-tech suit of armor to escape captivity and save his own life after a severe chest
        injury.</p>
    <p>*The Tech: Invented groundbreaking technologies, including the clean-energy Arc Reactor, advanced <b>artificial
            intelligence</b> (JARVIS), and time-travel mechanics.</p>
    <p>*Avengers Initiative: Played a crucial role in forming the Avengers, a team of superheroes assembled to protect
        the world from various threats.</p>
    <p>*Infinity War and Endgame: <strong>Sacrificed himself to defeat the villain.</strong></p>

    <h2>Words That Inspire</h2>
    <p>
        <blockqoute><i><q>I am Iron Man.</q></i>
        </blockqoute>
    </p>
    <p>These narcissistic words were uttered in the final seconds of the first film <b>Iron Man (2008)</b>. In context
        of the film these words can be seen as a declaration born from Tony Strak's boastful, self-aborbed playboy
        persona.</p>
    <p>A clear showcase of this persona is shown in another of his qoute <q><strong>Genius, billionaire, playboy,
                philanthropist. </strong></q></p>
    <p>However, in the context of the entire Marvel Cinematic Universe, these words take on a much deeper meaning. They
        represent Tony Stark's acceptance of his identity as a hero and his willingness to take responsibility for his
        actions. It is a moment of self-realization and growth for the character, as he embraces his role as a protector
        of the world and a member of the Avengers. The phrase has since become iconic and is often associated with Tony
        Stark's character and his journey throughout the Marvel Cinematic Universe.</p>
    <p>And yet, in a play of cinematic genius these words were flipped during the events of <b>Avengers: Endgame
            (2019)</b>.</p>
    <P>Instead of an arrogant boast, it becomes a final, unifying acceptance of responsibility, showing how he evolved
        from someone who built weapons for personal glory to a true hero.</P>

    <h3>Additional Information</h3>
    <p>
        <blockqoute><i><q>I am Iron Man.</q></i>
        </blockqoute>
    </p>
    <p>These words were also said in <b>Iron Man 3 (2013)</b> where they become an anxious admission that he is
        <i>nothing</i> without his suit.</p>

    <h3>Full Quote</h3>
    <p>
        <blockqoute><i><q>My armor, it was never a distraction or a hobby, it was a cocoon. And now, I'm a changed man.
                    You can take away my house, all my tricks and toys. But one thing you can't take away… I am Iron
                    Man."</q></i>
        </blockqoute>
    </p></q>


    <h2>My Reflection</h2>
    <p>Getting in the Marvel Cinematic Universe was only possible by the push from my older sister. With her
        encouragement, I found myself immersed in a world of superheroes and their incredible journeys.</p>
    <p>During my adventure in the franchise, I have come to appreciate the complexity and depth of the characters and
        their stories. Tony Stark, in particular, stands out as a character who embodies growth and redemption. His
        journey from a self-centered billionaire to a selfless hero is truly inspiring.</p>
    <p>Another favourite part of mine is his relationship with Peter Parker "Spider-Man". It shows the importance of
        mentorship and the impact one person can have on another's life, even after death.</p>


